# Title: Import LDAP Data Interchange Format File Via Ldifde.EXE
# Author: @gott_cyber
# Date: 2022-09-02
# Level: medium
# Description: Detects the execution of "Ldifde.exe" with the import flag "-i". The can be abused to include HTTP-based arguments which will allow the arbitrary download of files from a remote server.
# MITRE Tactic: Command and Control
# Tags: attack.command-and-control, attack.stealth, attack.t1218, attack.t1105
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_ldifde_file_load.yml
# False Positives:
#   - Since the content of the files are unknown, false positives are expected

CommandLine="*-i*" CommandLine="*-f*" Image="*\\ldifde.exe" OR OriginalFileName="ldifde.exe"